              76 percent of consumers have entered a store they&rsquo;d never visited before based solely on the sign (FedEx Office / ORC International survey). 68 percent have purchased because a sign caught their eye. And 52 percent said they&rsquo;re less willing to enter a store whose sign is poorly made or hard to read.
